{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idab8c872b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s10214"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"10214"},"text":"§ 10214.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Adjutants general and assistant adjutants general: reference to other officers of National Guard","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In any case in which, under the laws of a State, an officer of the National Guard of that jurisdiction, other than the adjutant general or an assistant adjutant general, normally performs the duties of that office, the references in sections 12004(b)(1), 12215, 12642(c), 14507(b), 14508(h), and 14512 of this title to the adjutant general or the assistant adjutant general shall be applied to that officer instead of to the adjutant general or assistant adjutant general.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idab8c872c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/dA/tXVI/s1661/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, div. A, title XVI, § 1661(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/2979"},"text":"108 Stat. 2979","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/383/dA/tX/s1075/b/51"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–383, div. A, title X, § 1075(b)(51)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-01-07"},"text":"Jan. 7, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/4371"},"text":"124 Stat. 4371","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idab8c872d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idab8c872